Program: Discovery
Title: What is Life - part four
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrz1w
Last Broadcast Date: 30 August 2005
How the cell took a central position in biological thought. The discovery of the cell is not as straightforward as many of the scientific breakthroughs of the last few hundred years. It took many years before living matter was considered to be compartmentalised.